The paper discusses a framework for model-based synthesis of optimal adaptation strategies for autonomous systems, which involves the use of Markov Decision Processes (MDPs) and goal-oriented techniques for requirement elicitation, refinement, and analysis. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories, as these areas are relevant to the development and management of autonomous systems. Additionally, the paper may also be relevant to the Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) and Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-categories, as it involves the use of models and languages for describing self-adaptive systems.
